Use 
this.setState(prevState => ({value: prevState.value + 1})) 
instead of 
this.setState({value: this.state.value + 1})
https://jiyeonseo.github.io/2018/07/16/no-state-in-setstate/



36:11  error  Missing an explicit type attribute for button    react/button-has-type
add type="button", "submit", "reset"
Submit submits data of a form(e.g. accept todo edit, login, etc)
Reset resets data of a form(e.g. reset todo edit)
Everything else should be button

31:20  error    Arrow function should not return assignment    no-return-assign
ref={(ref) => {this.pond = ref}}
to
ref={(ref) => {this.pond = ref}}


